<br>
So, I slide over to the other side of the graveyard and ask if that group minds if I just sit and watch. np comes the reply from two of them, so I watch for just a bit. Sunddenly comes a toon turing around and looking at me twice, and, yep, in comes the invite. I politly thank them for taking on a charity case, and the fun begins. The drops STUNK for the mobs we were pulling (gnarled treants, vunerable spiders and blackbirds). I was the low toon at about 8 levels below the next lowest, and with two over 60. xp would be classified as &quot;good&quot;, and would almost certainly have been &quot;GREAT&quot; for someone in the low to mid 50's, and not bad beyond that. The occasional bat was blue to me, and everything else was red.<br>
<br>
The aggro was the most interesting thing. I was definitely getting some level related aggro when meleeing. I was, however, only in danger about 3 times and never died. Image Sing's surprise however when he took his first ever quad at about 250-350 a pop - OUCH. Got hit once for 425 or  so. Most of the time, aggro was very managable, and I actually did contribute to the group - successfully backing up roles in all sorts of different ways - was easily the most challenge I've seen as a bard in a very, very long time. Mana, resists, cantana, DoT, haste, slow/snare (mine's combined) - they all showed up mixed in quite frequently last night. WOW. This and melee too much of the time. FUN TIMES.<br>
<br>
Couple of notes: A 48 bard is underpowered there, but I would almost agree with the assertion that I've heard that a bard is about the only thing likely to get picked up in the planes at 48. The versitility and the mana were the reasons I got invited (that and just plain mercy case). Personally, I'd say low 50's minimum for most classes, and 55+ minimum for true tanks (heavy aggro folks). I can see rangers and moks doing fine there a few levels sooner. Clerics would probably get picked up if they are high enough to get there (46+) - 49+ almost for sure I would think.<br>
<br>
Sing<br>
