<br>
Nobody wants a 90% rez.  And I dont like recruiting any class under 55.<br>
<br>
The cleric's rez is their strongest asset - shammys/chanties are the most in demand with their incredible slows then probably bards.  I am reluctant to recruit chanties under 59 - when their mez is resisted- the add will usually attack them or me if I have healed someone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=singsang>SingSang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 989<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(11/15/02 2:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/Sing-B.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fun in PoN</span><hr size=1> Hmmm. Good info as always.<br>
<br>
Indeed my slows (my combined slow/snare) was landing on most mobs most of the time. It was seriously invaluable when our Shammy LD'd once, then was OOM, then had to log. The haste was critical when the chanty LD'd and didn't come back. You get the drift - I was a busy bard.<br>
<br>
I was basically kidding when I went LFG, and was pretty surprised to see the invite. Felt bad for those first several minutes while I was trying to feel my way through what was working for me. Was good times in the end tho.<br>
<br>
My closest call with death came on a major overpull from our tank. It was his first trip to the planes also, and he grabbed two trees and one of those super killer blackbirds at once. We were getting some major slicing and dicing, then an add, and our 61 chanty was having problems getting it all under control. No evac, tho evac was called (doesn't work there perhaps?). Fortunately, we were already at graveyard, and most of us zoned easily. Two died, but at least one was because it was also her first time there, and she hadn't taken the time to find the zone out (I had first think). She died about 20 feet from it with no clue where it was. Oops.<br>
<br>
Like I said - good times though. Actually, some of the best group fun I've had in ages. Only other particularly fun group I've had recently was Atat, Perinn, Thallus and I in KC with a few comers and goers (including one that literally fell asleep at his keyboard, so we ultimately wound up disbanding him. He suddenly moved about 10 minutes later and was one seriously embarrased chanty - lol). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arathainkelvar>ArathainKelvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guild Leader</span><br>  Posts: 640<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(11/18/02 4:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/Arathain_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fun in PoN</span><hr size=1> I had a lot of fun as main tank in PoN for a group of 2 clerics (thanks god, lol) including ursi, a 61 chanter, 60 mage, and 61 necro.  As was my first time up there, I pulled what looked like a good target, which turned out to be a druid mob (fish thing).  Was dead before I got back to camp.  Tough zone, but I do believe some lower levels could help if the rest of the group is pretty well balanced and relatively high level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=24.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=24.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?top